{
  "version": 2,
  "buildCommand": "cd client && npm install && npm run build",
  "outputDirectory": "client/dist",
  "installCommand": "cd client && npm install",
  "framework": null,
  "rewrites": [
    {
      "source": "/(.*)",
      "destination": "/index.html"
    }
  ],
  "env": {
    "VITE_API_URL": "https://loggin-64qr.onrender.com"
  }
}

INSTRUCTIONS:
1. Rename this file to "vercel.json" when uploading to GitHub
2. This configuration forces frontend-only deployment
3. Fixes the issue where Vercel builds both frontend and backend